parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. In some cases, transmission failure can also lead to fires, which can cause damage to the vehicle and potentially harm occupants.
symptoms: The transmission jumps into low gear
the transmission fluid leaks through the breather vent
and spills onto the cross member exhaust pipe.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Axle and Ball Joint Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front axle and ball joints can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
The failure of the serpentine belt can cause the engine to overheat, leading to premature wear on engine components, and potentially causing the engine to seize or fail.
symptoms: The serpentine belt breaks or cracks

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the crankshaft pulley can cause the serpentine belt to fail, leading to engine overheating, and potentially causing the engine to seize or fail.
symptoms: The crankshaft pulley breaks or cracks
the serpentine belt breaks or cracks

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cracking of the engine block can cause engine oil leaks, coolant leaks, and engine failure, leading to expensive repairs and potentially causing accidents due to loss of vehicle control.
A stuck thermostat can cause the engine to overheat, leading to premature wear on engine components, and potentially causing the engine to seize or fail.
Leaking head gaskets can cause engine oil leaks, coolant leaks, and engine overheating, leading to expensive repairs and potentially causing accidents due to loss of vehicle control.

The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause a loss of brake fluid, leading to a soft or spongy brake pedal, and potentially resulting in extended stopping distances, accidents, or loss of control.
symptoms: Brake pedal goes to the floor
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
grinding noises when applying the brakes

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt anchors can cause the seat belts to malfunction, leading to a increased risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt anchors are broken
the seat belts will not hold in place
the seat belts do not fit properly.
